{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 3 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:1",
      "text": "ALEPH. I am the man that sees poverty, through the rod of his wrath upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:2",
      "text": "He has taken me, and led me away into darkness, and not into light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:3",
      "text": "Nay, against me has he turned his hand all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:4",
      "text": "He has made old my flesh and my skin; he has broken my bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:5",
      "text": "BETH. He has built against me, and compassed my head, and brought travail upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:6",
      "text": "He has set me in dark places, as them that have long been dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:7",
      "text": "He has builded against me, and I cannot come forth: he has made my brazen chain heavy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:8",
      "text": "GIMEL. Yea, though I cry and shout, he shuts out my prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:9",
      "text": "DALETH. He has built up my ways, he has hedged my paths;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:10",
      "text": "he has troubled me, as a she-bear lying in wait: he is to me as a lion in secret places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:11",
      "text": "He pursued me after I departed, and brought me to a stand: he has utterly ruined me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:12",
      "text": "HE. He has bent his bow, and set me as a mark for the arrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:13",
      "text": "He has caused the arrows of his quiver to enter into my reins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:14",
      "text": "I became a laughing-stock to all my people; and their song all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:15",
      "text": "VAU. He has filled me with bitterness, he has drenched me with gall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:16",
      "text": "And he has dashed out my teeth with gravel, he has fed me with ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:17",
      "text": "He has also removed my soul from peace: I forgot prosperity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:18",
      "text": "Therefore my success has perished, and my hope from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:19",
      "text": "ZAIN. I remembered by reason of my poverty, and because of persecution my bitterness and gall shall be remembered;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:20",
      "text": "and my soul shall meditate with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:21",
      "text": "This will I lay up in my heart, therefore I will endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:22",
      "text": "HETH. It is the mercies of the Lord, that he has not failed me, because his compassions are not exhausted. Pity us, O Lord, early every month: for we are not brought to an end, because his compassions are not exhausted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:23",
      "text": "They are new every morning: great is thy faithfulness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:24",
      "text": "The Lord is my portion, says my soul; therefore will I wait for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:25",
      "text": "TETH. The Lord is good to them that wait for him: the soul which shall seek him",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:26",
      "text": "is good, and shall wait for, and quietly expect salvation of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:27",
      "text": "TETH. It is good for a man when he bears a yoke in his youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:28",
      "text": "He will sit alone, and be silent, because he has borne it upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:29",
      "text": "JOD. He will give his cheek to him that smites him: he will be filled full with reproaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:31",
      "text": "For the Lord will not reject for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:32",
      "text": "CHAPH. For he that has brought down will pity, and that according to the abundance of his mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:33",
      "text": "He has not answered in anger from his heart, though he has brought low the children of a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:34",
      "text": "LAMED. To bring down under his feet all the prisoners of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:35",
      "text": "to turn aside the judgement of a man before the face of the Most High,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.36",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:36",
      "text": "to condemn a man unjustly in his judgement, the Lord has not given commandment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.37",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:37",
      "text": "Who has thus spoken, and it has come to pass? the Lord has not commanded it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.38",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:38",
      "text": "Out of the mouth of the Most High there shall not come forth evil and good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.39",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:39",
      "text": "MEM. Why should a living man complain, a man concerning his sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.40",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:40",
      "text": "NUN. Our way has been searched out and examined, and we will turn to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.41",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:41",
      "text": "Let us lift up our hearts with our hand to the lofty One in heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.42",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:42",
      "text": "We have sinned, we have transgressed; and thou hast not pardoned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.43",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:43",
      "text": "SAMECH. Thou has visited us in wrath, and driven us away: thou has slain, thou has not pitied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.44",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:44",
      "text": "Thou hast veiled thyself with a cloud because of prayer, that I might be blind,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.45",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:45",
      "text": "and be cast off. AIN. Thou hast set us alone in the midst of the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.46",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:46",
      "text": "All our enemies have opened their mouth against us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.47",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:47",
      "text": "Fear and wrath are come upon us, suspense and destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.48",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:48",
      "text": "Mine eye shall pour down torrents of water, for the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.49",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:49",
      "text": "PHE. Mine eye is drowned with tears, and I will not be silent, so that there shall be no rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.50",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:50",
      "text": "until the Lord look down, and behold from heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.51",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:51",
      "text": "Mine eye shall prey upon my soul, because of all the daughters of the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.52",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:52",
      "text": "TSADE. The fowlers chased me as a sparrow, all mine enemies destroyed my life in a pit without cause,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.53",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:53",
      "text": "and laid a stone upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.54",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:54",
      "text": "Water flowed over my head: I said, I am cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.55",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:55",
      "text": "KOPH. I called upon thy name, O Lord, out of the lowest dungeon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.56",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:56",
      "text": "Thou heardest my voice: close not thine ears to my supplication.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.57",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:57",
      "text": "Thou drewest nigh to my help: in the day wherein I called upon thee thou saidst to me, Fear not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.58",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:58",
      "text": "RECHS. O Lord, thou has pleaded the causes of my soul; thou has redeemed my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.59",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:59",
      "text": "Thou hast seen, O Lord, my troubles: thou hast judged my cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.60",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:60",
      "text": "Thou hast seen all their vengeance, thou hast looked on all their devices against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.61",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:61",
      "text": "CHSEN. Thou hast heard their reproach and all their devices against me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.62",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:62",
      "text": "the lips of them that rose up against me, and their plots against me all the day;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.63",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:63",
      "text": "their sitting down and their rising up: look thou upon their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.64",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:64",
      "text": "Thou wilt render them a recompense, O Lord, according to the works of their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.65",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:65",
      "text": "THAU. Thou wilt give them as a covering, the grief of my heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.3.66",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:66",
      "text": "Thou wilt persecute them in anger, and wilt consume them from under the heaven, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
